        "behavior": "; 7400 — quad 2-input NAND gate. Derived from the function table\n; (datasheet Table 3): each output nY is LOW only when both of that gate's\n; inputs are HIGH, and HIGH otherwise.\n;\n; This is a subunit (multi-gate) package: the four gates are independent,\n; so the behavior is one sum-of-products equation per unit, each using that\n; unit's own pin names. (renderas: nand fixes the drawn symbol; these\n; equations are the authoritative logic.)\n;\n; Equations are physical-level GALasm: '/' is the complement operator and\n; signal names are this file's pin names with any active-low '/' prefix\n; dropped (no input here is active-low). Outputs are active-high, so NAND\n; is written at the output's declared polarity using De Morgan:\n; nY = /nA + /nB (\"nY is HIGH when nA is LOW or nB is LOW\").\n1Y = /1A + /1B\n2Y = /2A + /2B\n3Y = /3A + /3B\n4Y = /4A + /4B\n",
        "description": "Quad 2-input NAND gate",
